    {"parentUuid":"1a52e1d9-8f63-4ade-bfad-3f0d86add620","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"0d330919-a8e5-4f46-8c87-22d9293c984b","agentId":"a7bc970e2fde4fc3a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Nqpr2Uhp3tn8ZTZsamGrBx","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# THE FORMULA FOR THE NTH PRIME NUMBER\n2\t\n3\t## Executive Summary\n4\t\n5\t**p(n) is computed exactly using mathematical function evaluation — no bruteforcing.**\n6\t\n7\t### Best Implementation: V10 (C-Accelerated)\n8\t\n9\t```\n10\tp(n) = min { x ∈ Z+ : π(x) ≥ n }\n11\t```\n12\t\n13\twhere π(x) is computed via C-accelerated Lucy_Hedgehog DP (no recursion),\n14\tand the target x is found via Newton + bisection root-finding.\n15\t\n16\t**File: `v10_c_accelerated.py`** (dual-mode: exact + approximate)\n17\t\n18\t---\n19\t\n20\t## Two Modes\n21\t\n22\t### EXACT MODE — 100% Accurate\n23\t\n24\tUses C-accelerated Lucy DP. Complexity: O(p(n)^{2/3}).\n25\t\n26\t| n | p(n) | Time |\n27\t|---|------|------|\n28\t| 10^3 | 7,919 | 0.000s |\n29\t| 10^5 | 1,299,709 | 0.006s |\n30\t| 10^7 | 179,424,673 | 0.034s |\n31\t| 10^8 | 2,038,074,743 | 0.140s |\n32\t| 10^9 | 22,801,763,489 | 0.175s |\n33\t\n34\t### APPROXIMATE MODE — First ~47% of Digits\n35\t\n36\tUses R^{-1}(n) via mpmath. Complexity: O(polylog(n)).\n37\t\n38\t| n | Time | Digits | Correct |\n39\t|---|------|--------|---------|\n40\t| 10^10 | 1.5s | 12 | ~5 |\n41\t| 10^50 | 0.14s | 53 | ~25 |\n42\t| 10^100 | 0.32s | 103 | ~50 |\n43\t| 10^200 | 1.15s | 203 | ~99 |\n44\t\n45\t---\n46\t\n47\t## The Three Components\n48\t\n49\t### 1. Initial Estimate: R^{-1}(n)\n50\t\n51\t```\n52\tR(x) = Σ_{k=1}^{49} μ(k)/k · li(x^{1/k})\n53\tli(x) = γ + ln(ln x) + Σ_{k=1}^∞ (ln x)^k / (k · k!)\n54\tR^{-1}(n): solve R(x) = n via Newton's method\n55\t```\n56\t\n57\tError: |R^{-1}(n) - p(n)| ~ O(√p(n) · ln(p(n))) under RH.\n58\t\n59\t### 2. Exact Prime Counting: Lucy_Hedgehog DP\n60\t\n61\t```\n62\tInitialize: S[v] = v - 1 for all v = ⌊N/k⌋\n63\tFor each prime p ≤ √N:\n64\t    S[v] -= S[v/p] - π(p-1)   for all v ≥ p²\n65\tResult: S[N] = π(N)\n66\t```\n67\t\n68\tITERATIVE (no recursion). O(N^{2/3}/ln N) time, O(√N) space.\n69\t\n70\t### 3. Root-Finding: Newton + Bisection\n71\t\n72\t```\n73\tx₀ = R^{-1}(n)                              [O(polylog)]\n74\txᵢ = xᵢ₋₁ + (n - π(xᵢ₋₁)) · ln(xᵢ₋₁)    [Newton, ~4 steps]\n75\tBisect [lo, hi]                              [~6 steps in ~70 integers]\n76\t```\n77\t\n78\t---\n79\t\n80\t## Why p(10^100) in 1 Second Is Impossible\n81\t\n82\tAfter **40+ approaches** across 3 sessions, the fundamental barrier:\n83\t\n84\t1. **Information gap**: R^{-1}(n) gives ~50/103 digits; 178 bits remain unknown\n85\t2. **Random walk**: δ(n) = p(n) - R^{-1}(n) is unpredictable (autocorr 0.996)\n86\t3. **Zeta zeros**: Need ~10^48 zeros for exact π at x ~ 10^102\n87\t4. **Computation**: Best methods need O(10^51) to O(10^68) operations\n88\t5. **Physics limit**: 10^42 to 10^59 times more than available in 1 second\n89\t\n90\tSee FINDINGS.md and THEOREM.md for complete analysis.\n91\t\n92\t---\n93\t\n94\t## Implementation\n95\t\n96\t```python\n97\tfrom v10_c_accelerated import nth_prime_exact, nth_prime_approx\n98\t\n99\t# EXACT (up to ~10^9 in seconds)\n100\tprint(nth_prime_exact(1000000, pi_func))  # 15485863\n101\t\n102\t# APPROXIMATE (any n, ~47% digits correct)\n103\tprint(nth_prime_approx(10**100))  # ~50 correct digits\n104\t```\n105\t\n106\t---\n107\t\n108\t## All Approaches Explored (40+)\n109\t\n110\tSee FINDINGS.md for the complete list across 3 sessions.\n111\t"}]},"uuid":"778a0852-e6b3-4f52-9f7b-1178337e603a","timestamp":"2026-04-04T04:44:57.321Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"1a52e1d9-8f63-4ade-bfad-3f0d86add620","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/apps/aplikacijos/prime-research","sessionId":"00538385-e056-4e78-8f42-1ce75c0130f0","version":"2.1.92","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"purrfect-gliding-lagoon"}
