    {"parentUuid":"3010f9be-8c28-4aa3-93b8-27f17f9bccae","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"0d330919-a8e5-4f46-8c87-22d9293c984b","agentId":"a7bc970e2fde4fc3a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01A597gEx6XVbvLBGw2Jhywn","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"\n2\tV10: C-ACCELERATED NTH PRIME SOLVER\n3\t=====================================\n4\tUses ctypes to call a C implementation of Lucy_Hedgehog DP\n5\tfor maximum performance. Also implements the analytical formula\n6\tfor p(n) that works in O(polylog(n)) time but gives only ~47% of digits.\n7\t\n8\tTWO MODES:\n9\t  1. EXACT MODE: Uses C-accelerated Lucy DP. 100% accurate. O(p(n)^{2/3}).\n10\t     Works up to p(10^12) in reasonable time.\n11\t\n12\t  2. APPROXIMATE MODE: Uses R^{-1}(n) via mpmath. O(polylog(n)) time.\n13\t     Gives first ~47% of digits correctly.\n14\t     p(10^100) in 0.5 seconds (approximate).\n15\t     p(10^1000) in ~2 seconds (approximate).\n16\t\"\"\"\n17\t\n18\timport math\n19\timport time\n20\timport ctypes\n21\timport tempfile\n22\timport os\n23\timport subprocess\n24\timport sys\n25\t\n26\t# ============================================================\n27\t# C implementation of Lucy DP (compiled at runtime)\n28\t# ============================================================\n29\t\n30\tLUCY_C_CODE = r\"\"\"\n31\t#include <stdio.h>\n32\t#include <stdlib.h>\n33\t#include <math.h>\n34\t\n35\tlong long lucy_pi(long long x) {\n36\t    if (x < 2) return 0;\n37\t    if (x < 3) return 1;\n38\t\n39\t    long long sqrtx = (long long)sqrt((double)x);\n40\t    while ((sqrtx + 1) * (sqrtx + 1) <= x) sqrtx++;\n41\t    while (sqrtx * sqrtx > x) sqrtx--;\n42\t\n43\t    long long *small = (long long*)calloc(sqrtx + 2, sizeof(long long));\n44\t    long long *large = (long long*)calloc(sqrtx + 2, sizeof(long long));\n45\t\n46\t    if (!small || !large) {\n47\t        if (small) free(small);\n48\t        if (large) free(large);\n49\t        return -1;\n50\t    }"}]},"uuid":"bbc9d5cc-0170-4cb2-b5fa-e06f91bfbef9","timestamp":"2026-04-04T04:45:03.247Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"3010f9be-8c28-4aa3-93b8-27f17f9bccae","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/apps/aplikacijos/prime-research","sessionId":"00538385-e056-4e78-8f42-1ce75c0130f0","version":"2.1.92","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"purrfect-gliding-lagoon"}
    {"parentUuid":"bbc9d5cc-0170-4cb2-b5fa-e06f91bfbef9","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a7bc970e2fde4fc3a","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018fqkcveGejPj9PNA7oy8AU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KcPDQUswreNUDjNEs4P1EJ","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/apps/aplikacijos/prime-research/THEOREM.md","limit":80},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5075,"cache_read_input_tokens":8245,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5075,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZi81dkrzXicmRkpvzCcR","type":"assistant","uuid":"c8b7de55-3b5b-4954-9dda-f7ce526e0291","timestamp":"2026-04-04T04:45:03.336Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/apps/aplikacijos/prime-research","sessionId":"00538385-e056-4e78-8f42-1ce75c0130f0","version":"2.1.92","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"purrfect-gliding-lagoon"}
    {"parentUuid":"c8b7de55-3b5b-4954-9dda-f7ce526e0291","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"0d330919-a8e5-4f46-8c87-22d9293c984b","agentId":"a7bc970e2fde4fc3a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KcPDQUswreNUDjNEs4P1EJ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Exact nth Prime: Computational Theory and Best Known Methods\n2\t\n3\t## Discovery/Analysis Date: 2026-04-03/04 (Sessions 1-3)\n4\t\n5\t## Status: BEST KNOWN SOLUTION — 100% exact, O(p(n)^{2/3})\n6\t\n7\t---\n8\t\n9\t## THE FUNDAMENTAL THEOREM (Session 3 Conclusion)\n10\t\n11\t### Theorem (Informal): No O(polylog(n)) algorithm for p(n) exists.\n12\t\n13\t**Evidence:**\n14\t1. Computing p(n) reduces to computing π(x) at O(1) points near R^{-1}(n)\n15\t2. Computing π(x) requires either:\n16\t   - O(x^{2/3}) combinatorial work (Deleglise-Rivat / Lucy DP)\n17\t   - O(x^{1/2+ε}) analytic work (Lagarias-Odlyzko, requires zeta zeros)\n18\t3. The correction δ(n) = p(n) - R^{-1}(n) is a random walk (proven empirically\n19\t   with autocorrelation 0.996 at lag 1, zero predictability from n)\n20\t4. The explicit formula Σ_ρ R(x^ρ) requires O(√x) zeros for error < 1\n21\t5. Aggarwal (2025) proved binary search on π(x) is asymptotically optimal\n22\t\n23\t### Corollary: p(10^100) in 1 second is IMPOSSIBLE.\n24\tRequired: O(10^68) combinatorial or O(10^51) analytic operations.\n25\tAvailable: O(10^9) operations in 1 second.\n26\tGap: Factor of 10^42 to 10^59.\n27\t\n28\t---\n29\t\n30\t## Best Working Solution: V7 Optimized Hybrid\n31\t\n32\t**File: `v7_optimized.py`**\n33\t\n34\t### Algorithm\n35\t\n36\t```\n37\tINPUT: n (positive integer)\n38\tOUTPUT: p(n) (the nth prime)\n39\t\n40\t1. x₀ ← R⁻¹(n)                     [O(polylog(n))]\n41\t   Newton's method on R(x) = n\n42\t   Error: |x₀ - p(n)| < 30 for n < 10^8\n43\t\n44\t2. NEWTON REFINEMENT:                [O(x₀^{2/3}) per step, ~4 steps]\n45\t   Repeat:\n46\t     π ← Lucy_DP(x₀)               [Exact π(x₀) via iterative DP]\n47\t     IF π = n AND isPrime(x₀): RETURN x₀\n48\t     x₀ ← x₀ + (n - π) · ln(x₀)   [Newton step on π⁻¹]\n49\t   Until bracket [lo, hi] found\n50\t\n51\t3. BISECTION:                        [~6 steps within ~70-integer interval]\n52\t   Binary search [lo, hi] using Lucy_DP\n53\t   Find smallest x with π(x) ≥ n\n54\t\n55\t4. WALK DOWN to prime:               [O(ln²(x)) steps]\n56\t   While not isPrime(x): x ← x - 1\n57\t   RETURN x\n58\t```\n59\t\n60\t### Components\n61\t\n62\t| Component | Method | Complexity |\n63\t|-----------|--------|-----------|\n64\t| Initial estimate | R^{-1} via Newton | O(polylog(n)) |\n65\t| π(x) evaluation | Lucy_Hedgehog DP | O(x^{2/3}/ln(x)), O(√x) space |\n66\t| Root finding | Newton + bisection | ~10 π evaluations |\n67\t| Primality test | Deterministic Miller-Rabin | O(log³(x)) |\n68\t\n69\t### What It Does NOT Do\n70\t\n71\t| Eliminated | How |\n72\t|-----------|-----|\n73\t| Recursion | Lucy DP is bottom-up iterative |\n74\t| Sieve arrays | DP uses O(√x) not O(x) |\n75\t| Full enumeration | Only ~10 π evaluations, not O(n) |\n76\t| Primality testing of many numbers | Only ~70 tests in last step |\n77\t\n78\t### Performance\n79\t\n80\t| n | p(n) | Time | π evaluations |"}]},"uuid":"5c83a741-8923-48ce-8a1a-1dbff20a8db6","timestamp":"2026-04-04T04:45:03.344Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c8b7de55-3b5b-4954-9dda-f7ce526e0291","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/apps/aplikacijos/prime-research","sessionId":"00538385-e056-4e78-8f42-1ce75c0130f0","version":"2.1.92","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"purrfect-gliding-lagoon"}
